  "title": "Question on the page \"menu\"",
  "body": "Hi! I have a documentation issue on InstantSearch.js. I could not find what I was looking for on the page \"[menu](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/widgets/menu.html)\".\r\n\r\nItems in my dataset have a `category` property, with values `category1`, `category2`, `category3`.\r\n\r\nI'm trying to build a menu looking like:\r\n\r\n`[All categories] [category1] [category2] [category3]`\r\n\r\nWhat I could not achieve with the widget:\r\n- Menu items disappear when applying other filters but I want to keep them all (even if no result matches)\r\n- Clicking on a selected category unsets it (hence resets the filter), but I want to click on a specific button \"All categories\" to reset this particular category filter.\r\n\r\nCan the Menu widget fulfill my needs? \r\nOr should I hardcode the menu and trigger an Algolia query for each button?\r\n",
